<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Wentzel, Willard Ferdinand. A Continuation of the Journal of the Forks Mackenzie's River for Summer 1807-1808. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0022</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p></p>
<p class="head">June Cont<sup>d</sup> 1808</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">came from above<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Send the Keg of Gum &amp; 20 fms of Bark to M<sup>r</sup> Clarke<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Tues<sup>y</sup> 8<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Rained all day &#8211; NB. I forgot to mention that I had given particular order to the men, to send any Indians they Should meet with who had either Furrs or provisions to this Place as quick as possible &amp; to desire Grand Chefre &amp; Jollibois if they should see them to make all possible diligence, so that I might settle matters to go above<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Wednes<sup>y</sup> 9<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The weather Cleared up towards the afternoon, so that I made a Shift with the help of Smith &amp; Martin to put a Canoe on the Bed<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Thurs<sup>y</sup> 10<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sewed the Bottom seems of the Canoe &amp; tied on the maitres<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[W]</span>e had some Showers of rain<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Friday 11<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Got all the Barrs put to the Canoe &amp; the <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Poignees</span> sewed, which terminated this days business<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Satur<sup>y</sup> 12<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Put the <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Serres</span> in the Canoe &#8211; &amp; arranged Smith to be off tomorrow to go above in order to procure a few Provisions &amp; to put Courage in the natives, not to Despond at their not seeing up there, that I am only waiting for Grand Chefre &amp; Jollibois<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[G]</span>ave him 20 meas: Am<sup>n</sup> &amp; 12 flints to Trade<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Got 3 nets put in the water 5 days ago, in which time we have only taken 8 P<sup>s</sup> of very bad Fish<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Sun<sup>y</sup> 13<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Smith with all the young men I had here sett off in a Canoe Batard<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[G]</span>ave him 15<sup>lb</sup> of Dried m<sup>t</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Mon<sup>y</sup> 14<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Smith with Gentry returned with the meat of a Female de Carriboux &amp; her young one which they have Killed this morning above the rapids &#8211; value 6½ Skins<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[R]</span>ained a little to day, no Fish in the nets, The water in the Forks rising exceeding fast &amp; the Grand river is extremely low<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Tues<sup>y</sup> 15<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Smith launched out again<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  I cannot see what Keeps Jollibois so long away<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  I begin to fear that some melancholy accident has happened to him &#8211; for I don't</p>
<p style="text-align:right;">believe</p>

